# TanStack Query Hooks Pattern

## Folder Structure

Each data domain gets its own folder in `hooks/`:

```
hooks/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ series/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ queryKeys.ts      # Query key constants
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ useSeries.ts      # Query hooks (fetching)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ useSeriesMutations.ts  # Mutation hooks (create/update/delete)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.ts          # Barrel exports
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ README.md         # Documentation
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ articles/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ queryKeys.ts
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ useArticles.ts
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ useArticleMutations.ts
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.ts
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ README.md
```

## Query Keys (queryKeys.ts)

Always define query keys as constants:

```typescript
export const seriesKeys = {
  all: ['series'] as const,
  lists: () => [...seriesKeys.all, 'list'] as const,
  detail: (id: string) => [...seriesKeys.all, 'detail', id] as const,
  api: {
    all: ['/api/series'] as const,
    detail: (id: string) => ['/api/series', id] as const,
  },
} as const;
```

Benefits:
- Type safety and autocomplete
- Single source of truth
- Prevents typos
- Easy refactoring

## Query Hooks (useX.ts)

```typescript
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import { seriesKeys } from './queryKeys';

export interface Series {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  // ... other fields
}

export function useSeries() {
  return useQuery<Series[]>({
    queryKey: seriesKeys.api.all,
  });
}
```

## Mutation Hooks (useXMutations.ts)

```typescript
import { useMutation, useQueryClient } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import { seriesKeys } from './queryKeys';

export function useCreateSeries(adminToken?: string | null) {
  const queryClient = useQueryClient();
  return useMutation({
    mutationFn: (data) => apiRequest('POST', '/api/series', data, adminToken),
    onSuccess: () => {
      queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: seriesKeys.api.all });
    },
  });
}
```

## Index Exports (index.ts)

```typescript
export { useSeries, type Series } from './useSeries';
export { useCreateSeries, useUpdateSeries } from './useSeriesMutations';
export { seriesKeys } from './queryKeys';
```

## Usage in Components

```typescript
// Fetching data
import { useSeries } from '../hooks/series';

const { data: series = [], isLoading, error } = useSeries();

// Mutations (admin)
import { useCreateSeries } from '../hooks/series';

const createSeries = useCreateSeries(adminToken);
createSeries.mutate(newData, {
  onSuccess: () => console.log('Created!'),
});
```

## Loading States

Always add skeleton loaders when using queries:

```typescript
function MySkeleton() {
  return (
    <div className="animate-pulse">
      <div className="h-6 bg-gray-200 rounded w-20 mb-4"></div>
      {/* ... */}
    </div>
  );
}

function MyComponent() {
  const { data, isLoading } = useSeries();
  
  if (isLoading) return <MySkeleton />;
  // ...
}
```

## Rules

1. **One folder per data domain** - Don't mix series and articles hooks
2. **Always use queryKeys constants** - Never hardcode query key strings
3. **Export types from query hooks** - Keep interfaces with their data
4. **Invalidate on mutations** - Always call `invalidateQueries` in `onSuccess`
5. **Default to empty arrays** - Use `const { data = [] }` for list queries
6. **Add loading states** - Every query should have a skeleton/loading UI
7. **Keep mutations separate** - Query hooks and mutation hooks in separate files
8. **Document with README.md** - Each hooks folder needs documentation
